    {
        "id": "oauth2-comment-1",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "oauth2-auth-flow",
        "name": "OAuth2/Keycloak Configuration",
        "info": "Configure the api-config node with your Keycloak settings:\n\n1. **Keycloak URL**: Your Keycloak server (e.g., http://localhost:8080)\n2. **Realm**: The Keycloak realm name\n3. **Client ID**: The client application ID\n4. **Client Secret**: Stored securely in credentials\n\nThe api-server will:\n- Fetch JWKS from Keycloak automatically\n- Validate Bearer tokens on protected endpoints\n- Extract roles and scopes from token claims\n- Return 401 for missing/invalid tokens\n- Return 403 for insufficient permissions",
        "x": 210,
        "y": 40,
        "wires": []
    },
